FBIS3-53416 "drnes010_p_94003" FBIS-NES-94-010 Document Type:Daily Report 14 Jan 1994 SOUTH ASIA Afghanistan Islamic Parties Establish Propaganda Commission LD1401015494 Kabul Radio Afghanistan Network in Dari 1600 GMT 13 Jan 94 LD1401015494 Kabul Radio Afghanistan Network Language: Dari Article Type:BFN [Text] In the name of God, the compassionate, the merciful: At its session of 12 February, members of the coordination charter unanimously agreed on--because the propaganda jehad as well as the armed jehad are an objective necessity--a declaration of the coordination charter of the Islamic Parties of Afghanistan: to harmonize propaganda and give it the same direction in different fields and in various aspects of war; to exchange views and information; and to enlighten the public about current events and issues of the country in order that each one of the parties, members of the coordination charter, can participate in the supply and publication of news and to campaign against the propaganda of the enemy force. Therefore, we inform our compatriots about the establishment of a propaganda commission with the following details: Every party will introduce two of its literary and scholarly personalities for participation in the propaganda commission. Scholarly brothers of parties can send their scientific and political articles and texts to the propaganda commission. Islamic parties, members of the charter, [words indistinct]. Ulema, mosque prayer leaders, officials of shia ceremonial sites, and other brothers are asked to participate in the enlightening of the people of the city's wards as a religious duty. Radio and television staff are asked to harmonize their propaganda programs with the propaganda commission and [words indistinct].
